OL,3,CFire station demolition on hold as new
OL,4,Ccouncil debate ordered amid Gormley row
OL,6,FDeputy council leader Richard
OL,7,FWearmouth added that Sir Antony and
OL,8,Fhis foundation had "always been
OL,9,Fcompletely honest and open" about
OL,10,Ftheir proposals, which the committee
OL,11,Fheard were chiefly based on storage
OL,12,Fspace but could also feature public
OL,13,Fexhibitions, but that the issue had
OL,14,Fbecome "twisted" by others.
OL,16,FCllr Wearmouth said that the council
OL,17,Fwanted to continue working with the
OL,18,Fsculptor, who already has a studio and
OL,19,Ffoundry in Hexham, and hoped to find
OL,20,Fhim an alternative site closer to the
OL,21,Ftown centre.
